repo.description: The most widely used Python to C compiler
repo.name: cython

body:
Registering cdef classes with `collections.abs.sequence` only works to set the type flag if cdef classes are mutable. Unfortunately we want them to be immutable since it's possible to corrupt memory with mutable cdef classes (https://github.com/cython/cython/pull/5023).

Therefore, add a Cython directive for marking cdef classes as a sequence, but only allow it in utility code for now. This is a cutdown version of https://github.com/cython/cython/pull/5030 - I don't want to add new public features without consensus, but I do want to merge the fix for mutable classes. Therefore I'm adding the feature privately for now.

commit.message:
Allow setting type flags for pattern matching

via an additional decorator for cdef classes.

Closes #5027 and removes blocker for #5023

Fix tests

Py2 and line numbers

Don't mark the types as immutable

This is part of a separate PR and snuck in for testing
Make collection_type option internal only for now

title: Change how memoryviewslice/array has sequence flag set
